			<ns0:name>dmichael@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/dmichael@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Here's a good suggestion from Brett in an e-mail for how we might deal with this problem:
It seems like we need some kind of reset signal when the nexe is actually loaded so that Chrome clears its PPP_Instance interface pointer and re-queries, and then sends a new DidChangeView to the newly loaded plugin. The nacll plugin would fake the Instance interface before that (painting whatever loading notifications it may have), but after that would forward all GetInterface calls to the plugin before responding that the interface is supported.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-03-11T16:07:17.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-03-11T16:07:17.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 1 by dmichael@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1513#c1" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1513/comments/full/1" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>